name: Bookmarks
description: A plugin that adds bookmarking functionality.
longdescription:
This plugin enables a Binary Ninja user to bookmark addresses of interest and quickly navigate back to them at a later time. As the API for loading and saving user data to the analysis database is not available yet, the bookmarks must be manually saved and loaded to a separate file for now.

To install this plugin, navigate to your Binary Ninja plugins directory, and run

```git clone https://github.com/joshwatson/binaryninja-bookmarks.git bookmarks```

Then create a python file called `bookmarks.py` with the contents

```import bookmarks```

name: Jump table branch editor
author: jofra
description: A plugin that eases fixing jump table branches
longdescription:
This plugin allows you to easily edit the branches of an indirect jump. This is helpful in situations where binja fails to identify jump tables. To fix this, previously you would have to use the python console, but with this plugin you can do it from a simple UI.

You can insert the target addresses as a single addr (hex or decimal) (e.g. `0x2000` or `123`) or a comma separated list (e.g. `0x1d80, 0x1dc0, 0x1de0, 0x1df0, 0x1e00`).
